    "title": "gui: freezes on Ubuntu 20.04 when using a different data location",
    "body": "Hey, \r\nso I installed Bitcoin Core via the files provided on Bitcoin.org (Linux txz), on a fresh Ubuntu 20.04 VM. I followed the Instruction from the site too.\r\n\r\nWhen prompted with the \"Welcome\" window, I chose a different directory in a mounted SMB share. After clicking on \"Ok\", [Bitcoin Core will start but will stay on the loading screen](https://youtu.be/i7dz6nbEGOA). I did check the directory and Bitcoin Core did create a few files(no debug tho), so It has Read & Write permissions.  \r\n\r\nI tried it with the files from Bitcoin.org, Snap Store, and with the repo from luke-jr. Always getting the same error. When using the default settings, It works.\r\n\r\n[Also Bitcoin Core will not show anything in the window for searching a different directory.](https://youtu.be/BTjBAmWVEow)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
